<doc id="215252" wikidata="Q26261754" url="?curid=215252" title="Glomerulus">
<text>Glomerulus (; : glomeruli) is a common term used in anatomy to describe globular structures of entwined vessels, fibers, or neurons. &quot;Glomerulus&quot; is the diminutive of the Latin &quot;glomus&quot;, meaning &quot;ball of yarn&quot;.

&quot;Glomerulus&quot; may refer to:
* Glomerulus (kidney), the filtering unit of the kidney
* Glomerulus (olfaction), a structure in the olfactory bulb
* Glomerulus (cerebellum), the contact between specific cells in the cerebellum

== See also ==

